Configure a Salesforce CORS Allowed List for Query Workspaces

Add a requesting origin to the Cross-Origin Resource Sharing (CORS) allowed list for a Data Cloud org. It allows query workspace resources to connect to connected apps and supported Salesforce APIs from JavaScript code in a web browser.

REQUIRED USER PERMISSIONS
USER PERMISSION SET NEEDED
To configure the Salesforce CORS allowed list:	Data Cloud Admin
From Setup, in the Quick Find box, enter CORS, and select CORS.
Click New.
For the Origin URL Pattern:
Navigate to the Console tab in your Developer Tools of query workspaces. It displays an error.
Copy the origin URL on the Console tab and populate the Origin URL Pattern. The URL pattern is https://MyDomainName.lightning.force.com where MyDomainName is the My Domain name of your org. You can find your org’s My Domain name on the My Domain page in Setup.
Click Save.
Adding to the CORS allowed list can take up to 5 minutes.
